      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0649P0-03192'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0649P0_20030617_GCR_72' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        The noble Lord said: This clause accords the Secretary of State power to alter social security benefits in accordance with the transitional arrangements which will follow revaluation, reflecting a point made in the last amendment. The purpose of this amendment is simply to clarify with the Minister
        <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_240gc' title='Col. 240GC &mdash; HL Deb 17 June 2003 vol 649 c240GC' name='column_240gc' href='#column_240gc' rel='bookmark'>240GC</a>
        what opportunity Parliament will have to scrutinise any changes to social security benefits that may be consequent on these changes to council tax.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0649P0-03193'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0649P0_20030617_GCR_73' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
